SIMPLE: sinuosity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sinuosity
<hw>Sin`u*os"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Sinuosities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>sinuosit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Quality or state of
being sinuous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A bend, or a series of bends and turns; a winding,
or a series of windings; a wave line; a curve.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A line of coast certainly amounting, with its
<qex>sinuosities</qex>, to more than 700 miles.</q> <rj><qau>Sydney
Smith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinuous</ent>⟦br⟧
